    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame10" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="5.8937in" svg:y="0.0673in" svg:width="1in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="45">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="P5">Luce</text:p>
      <text:p text:style-name="P5">visibile</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame11" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="5.3646in" svg:y="0.0193in" svg:width="0.7417in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="47">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="P4">Anodo</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>Quando si fa incidere la luce si ha un passaggio di elettroni e quindi il condensatore inizia a caricarsi. La tensione <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame12" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="3.3957in" svg:y="0.778in" svg:width="0.7417in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="49">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:span text:style-name="T2"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">V</text:span></text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>che si genera ai capi del condensatore produce un campo elettrico tra il catodo e <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame13" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="5.9354in" svg:y="1.2799in" svg:width="1in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="48">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Fig. 3</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>l’anodo che si oppone al moto degli <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame14" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="5.3646in" svg:y="1.5193in" svg:width="1.0165in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="46">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="P4">Catodo</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>elettroni. Se l’energia <text:s/>posseduta dagli elettroni è sufficiente a superare la differenza di potenziale, allora il passaggio di corrente continua e il condensatore continua a caricarsi. Il processo si ferma quando la tensione <text:span text:style-name="T4"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">V</text:span> ai capi del condensatore, è tale che il prodotto <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr7" draw:name="Object7" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4217in" svg:height="0.222in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mi>q</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>e</mi>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
           <mi mathvariant="italic">ΔV</mi>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } ΔV} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD2gAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
